  "texts": [
    "With TZPC, a trusted application that identifies and blurs faces in video feeds would achieve Pd-Ros' goals.We do not expect all drone platforms to have the TZPC on their SoC.",
    "For example, the experimental platform (a NVidia Xavier NX development board) that we use to build Pd-Ros does not offer exclusive secure world access to peripherals.",
    "We therefore focus on how to achieve Pd-Ros' goals even if the SoC lacks TZPC support.",
    "In the absence of TZPC, the video footage from the camera is accessible in the normal world.",
    "The mechanisms introduced by Pd-Ros must therefore be tailored to the software environment executing in the normal world.With this TZPC-based design, the factors F1 and F2 discussed above do not apply (disregarding zero-day exploits against the secure world itself, as is standard, because it is part of the trustedcomputing base)."
  ],
